cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper deals with natural language processing and neural networks, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the ability of neural networks to acquire syntax, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve training RNNs, which is a type of neural network, and thus could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a synthetic approach to study the impact of typological properties on RNNs, which could be considered under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
